data.description: Don't miss this upgraded and inviting 2-bed, 2 bath residence in the sought after Del Webb 55+ community in Lakewood Ranch. Enjoy all the comforts of a well designed layout, coupled with a community tailored to an active and mature lifestyle. This home features an open floor plan with versatile DEN, perfect for an office or additional living space. Corinna Place is a charming cul-de-sac street featuring a tranquil enclave with minimal traffic. Upgrades and features of this impeccably maintained home include PGT WINGUARD HURRICANE IMPACT WINDOWS AND DOORS, extended screened lanai with 2 ceiling fans, Hunter Douglas window treatments in the owner's suite, dining room, guest bedroom, and den, professional landscaping, upgraded kitchen cabinets including roll-out shelving, FENCED back yard, over sized owner's suite closet with built in drawers and shelving, screened front porch entryway, epoxy garage floor, overhead storage shelf in garage, custom designed garage workbench and cabinets by Garage King, upgraded electrical/lighting package, ceiling fans in all rooms (6 total including lanai fans), whole house surge protector, Kinetico whole house water softening system with 3- stage reverse osmosis system at the sink (system does not require electricity), external hook-up and wiring for a portable generator, security system, 21 X 21 upgraded tile throughout (no carpeting in home), and a large cabinet in hallway niche at garage entry for additional storage. Entertaining is made easy with adjoining gathering room and kitchen with over 9 feet of kitchen island space. Zero corner sliding glass doors bring the outdoors inside maximizing the water and lush landscaped views. Love where you live within the tranquility of this esteemed 55+ community where upscale living meets the renowned beauty of Lakewood Ranch. Enjoy picturesque trails and nature while winding through beautifully landscaped park-like surroundings. Del Webb community at Lakewood Ranch boasts an array of amenities, including a state-of-the-art fitness center, inviting resort style swimming pool with lap lanes, 6 tennis courts, 8 pickleball courts, and 4 bocce ball courts. There is a second swimming pool approximately 1/2 mile from the property. The 21,000 + SF clubhouse offers multiple activity and gathering rooms, a group fitness studio, a catering kitchen, and card/game/billiards rooms. A full time lifestyle director keeps the party going with a variety of activities, clubs and events. The community often hosts events for a vibrant social scene. Dine or sip your favorite beverage from the bar at the Lake House restaurant; a perfect spot to relax while enjoying the stunning water views. Outdoors you will also find a fire pit, dog park, and horseshoe pit. For active adults, there is a club ready to welcome you, and the list of activities are endless! Additionally, golf enthusiasts can take advantage of nearby golf courses, completing the well-rounded lifestyle that Del Webb at Lakewood Ranch offers. Approximately 18 miles to the SRQ International Airport, approximately 63 miles to the Tampa International Airport, approximately 6 miles to the 36-acre lakefront town center of Waterside, and approximately 8 miles to the University Town Center dining/shopping mecca and the Nathan Benderson Park. Come see and experience for yourself this exceptional home and lifestyle!
